news.title: Approve plan for TNHB flats in Arumbakkam: NGT
news.para: The proposed project, which will have 304 dwelling units, is coming up on the banks of Cooum at an estimated cost of 400 crore.

news.title: Chhattisgarh government notifies amended rent control act
news.para: Under the Chhattisgarh Rent Control Act, the State Government appoints one or more officers not below the rank of a Deputy Collector, as Rent Controller with territorial jurisdiction as to be specified by the District Collector.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body sees 54% increase in property tax collection
news.para: The residents have a chance to avail a 10% rebate on the property tax till September 30, therefore rush is seen at the MC suvidha centres, at least before the lunch hours.

news.title: Greater Chennai Corporation waives 2% interest on property tax dues till October 15
news.para: The corporation had set a deadline of September 30 for paying tax dues for the first half of the financial year. Usually, if people do not pay taxes beyond the deadline, a 2% simple interest is added to the dues.

news.title: Nagpur: Set up EV charging station on premises, get 2% property tax rebate
news.para: According to the order, individuals will get a 2% rebate in property tax if they set up charging stations for their own vehicles and make the facility available to owners of other electric vehicles.

news.title: Nashik civic body to make names of property tax defaulters public
news.para: NMC’s property tax department officials said the names of defaulters will be uploaded on its website. This is likely to have an impact on the defaulters as others would come to know that they are defaulters, said the officials.

news.title: Secunderabad Cantonment Board directs RWAs to open locked gates, blocked lanes
news.para: In Cantonment, 100 colonies have blocked thoroughfares and put up gates and restricted residents of neighbouring colonies from accessing their internal roads.

news.title: Indore civic body to collect over 1.5 times property tax from defaulters
news.para: ​​​“The new amendment allows the Municipal Corporation to collect 1.5 to 2 times of the property tax from residential property owners in case of a delay,” IMC’s additional commissioner Bhavya Mittal said.

news.title: Chandigarh: Rs 8.9 crore for 500 sq yard plot in Sector 19
news.para: A 500 sq yard residential plot located in Sector 19 fetched Rs 8.90 crore against a reserve price of Rs 6.34 crore in the UT estate office property auction that concluded on Thursday. The estate office had offered 12 residential plots on freehold basis.

news.title: Mumbai: Respite for cooperative housing societies as AGMs & audit deadlines extended
news.para: According to housing society federations due to Covid, several societies took time till March this year to clear their audit for earlier fiscal 2020-21 and thus had a backlog for recently ended fiscal 2021-22 to be cleared yet.

news.title: YEIDA issues notices to ATS Group & Supertech to deposit Rs 332.6 crore in two weeks
news.para: Apart from ATS and Supertech, YEIDA has issued notices to 13 other allottees under the institutional category to clear Rs 2,377.2 crore in dues.

news.title: Noida: Structural audit policy for high-rise buildings set to take shape soon
news.para: ​Residents’ groups that participated in the meeting suggested that a survey should be carried out first in all highrise apartments to identify buildings that need audit as the exercise involves a huge cost.

news.title: ITAT-Mumbai holds market value of flat on agreement date as valid
news.para: Typically, when a home buyer books a flat, the purchase price is finalised on this date and is reflected in the allotment/agreement letter. Then, the buyer makes periodic payments over several months.

news.title: Macrotech aims to repay Yes Bank loan five months ahead of schedule
news.para: The board of Macrotech Developers will meet on September 30 (Friday) to approve the proposal of "prepayment of the outstanding principal amount of ₹125 crore, which is due on February 27, 2023, to Yes Bank, sole debenture holder," according to a stock exchange disclosure.

news.title: K Raheja Corp acquires 1.5-acre land in Mumbai's Sion for Rs 120 crore
news.para: An additional 0.4-acre land parcel adjoining this plot will also be acquired by the developer through a separate transaction later, as per the terms agreed upon between both the parties.
